import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    avg_yield_per_site = data.groupby('site')['yield'].mean()
    ax = avg_yield_per_site.plot(kind='bar', color='blue', alpha=0.7)
    plt.title('What is the average yield per site?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Site')
    plt.ylabel('Average Yield')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.legend(['Average Yield'])
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    data.boxplot(column='yield', by='variety', ax=ax)
    plt.title('How does the yield vary by variety?')
    plt.suptitle('')
    plt.xlabel('Variety')
    plt.ylabel('Yield')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.legend(title='Variety', loc='upper right')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['year'])]
    data['year'] = data['year'].dt.year

    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    for variety in data['variety'].unique():
        variety_data = data[data['variety'] == variety]
        plt.plot(variety_data['year'], variety_data['yield'], label=variety)

    plt.title('What is the trend of yield over the years?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Year')
    plt.ylabel('Yield')
    plt.legend(title='Variety', loc='best')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['yield'], bins=30, color='blue', alpha=0.7, label='Yield')
    plt.xlabel('Yield')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of yield across all sites and varieties?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    pivot_data = data.pivot_table(values='yield', index='site', columns='variety')
    ax = sns.heatmap(pivot_data, cmap='coolwarm', annot=True, fmt=".2f")
    plt.title('How does the yield vary by site and variety?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Variety')
    plt.ylabel('Site')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
